    "Another CI test for discrete BNs is mutual information (MI) which measures the amount of information shared between two variables (Cheng et al. 1997).",
    "The mutual information between two variables A and B is:",
    "where P(a, b) is shorthand for P(A = a, B = b), and similarly for P(a), and P(b).",
    "Condi- tional mutual information is defined as:",
    "where P(a, b|s) is shorthand forP(A = a, B = b| S 1 = s 1, …, S q = s q), and similarly for P(a|s) andP(b|s)."
